<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="482" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,440,935]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,513,539]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is a patronymic honoring Armando Ruiz Balcells, the first author’s grandfather.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="482" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,440,935]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,584,611]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo, 2020" authorityName="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo" authorityYear="2020" box="[434,576,585,611]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Nopsma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armandoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[434,576,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">N. armandoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[583,646,585,611]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[583,646,585,611]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo, 2020" authorityName="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo" authorityYear="2020" box="[869,994,586,611]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Nopsma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="enriquei" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[869,994,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">N. enriquei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1002,1064,585,611]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1002,1064,585,611]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the large tegulum reaching or exceeding the palpal tibia length but are readily recognized by having an short palpal tibia, just a little greater than patella length (
<figureCitation box="[318,397,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,957,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[159,1427,957,1886]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 17. Nopsma armandoi n. sp., male holotype (MCZ 125597). A Habitus, dorsal view. B Left palp, prolateral view. C Left palp, retrolateral view. D Habitus, ventral view. E Prosoma, ventral view. F Embolus, prolateral view. Scale bar: A, D (1mm); B–C, E–F (0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714710/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
B–C), and by the embolus projecting from the prolateral median surface of the tegulum, with three very thin, long projections on the tip (
<figureCitation box="[638,716,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,957,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[159,1427,957,1886]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 17. Nopsma armandoi n. sp., male holotype (MCZ 125597). A Habitus, dorsal view. B Left palp, prolateral view. C Left palp, retrolateral view. D Habitus, ventral view. E Prosoma, ventral view. F Embolus, prolateral view. Scale bar: A, D (1mm); B–C, E–F (0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714710/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
B–C, F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="483" pageId="21" pageNumber="482" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,440,935]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,336,728,755]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[351,408,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[425,529,729,756]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">holotype</typeStatus>
): Total length 7.6. Carapace 4.4 long, 3.5 wide. Sternum 3.6 long, 3.3 wide. Leg measurements: I: 3.95; II: 3.85; III: 3.5; IV: 4.25. Carapace orange-brown with weakly defined dorsal pattern (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,957,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[159,1427,957,1886]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 17. Nopsma armandoi n. sp., male holotype (MCZ 125597). A Habitus, dorsal view. B Left palp, prolateral view. C Left palp, retrolateral view. D Habitus, ventral view. E Prosoma, ventral view. F Embolus, prolateral view. Scale bar: A, D (1mm); B–C, E–F (0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714710/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae, palps, sternum orangish brown, endites, labium pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1155,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,957,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[159,1427,957,1886]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 17. Nopsma armandoi n. sp., male holotype (MCZ 125597). A Habitus, dorsal view. B Left palp, prolateral view. C Left palp, retrolateral view. D Habitus, ventral view. E Prosoma, ventral view. F Embolus, prolateral view. Scale bar: A, D (1mm); B–C, E–F (0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714710/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Fig. 17E</figureCitation>
), and legs orange-brown (
<figureCitation box="[159,262,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,957,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[159,1427,957,1886]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 17. Nopsma armandoi n. sp., male holotype (MCZ 125597). A Habitus, dorsal view. B Left palp, prolateral view. C Left palp, retrolateral view. D Habitus, ventral view. E Prosoma, ventral view. F Embolus, prolateral view. Scale bar: A, D (1mm); B–C, E–F (0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714710/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Fig. 17D</figureCitation>
); coxae and trochanters lighter. Abdomen pale gray with dorsal pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1160,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,957,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[159,1427,957,1886]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 17. Nopsma armandoi n. sp., male holotype (MCZ 125597). A Habitus, dorsal view. B Left palp, prolateral view. C Left palp, retrolateral view. D Habitus, ventral view. E Prosoma, ventral view. F Embolus, prolateral view. Scale bar: A, D (1mm); B–C, E–F (0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714710/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
). Anal tubercle and spinnerets lighter than abdomen. Copulatory bulb with a globose, large, oval tegulum and a long embolus projecting from the prolateral median surface of the tegulum, with three very thin, long projections on the tip (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1272,909,935]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,957,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[159,1427,957,1886]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 17. Nopsma armandoi n. sp., male holotype (MCZ 125597). A Habitus, dorsal view. B Left palp, prolateral view. C Left palp, retrolateral view. D Habitus, ventral view. E Prosoma, ventral view. F Embolus, prolateral view. Scale bar: A, D (1mm); B–C, E–F (0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714710/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
B–C, F).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714710" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3714710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714710/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="482" startId="21.[151,250,1905,1930]" targetBox="[159,1427,957,1885]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1905,2002]" pageId="21" pageNumber="482">
